\begin_layout Section
Lemniscate of Gerono
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The lemniscate of Gerono is given by the implict equation:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
x^{4}-a^{2}\left(x^{2}-y^{2}\right)=0\label{eq:4}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Parametrize with a substitution using a pencil of parabolas through (0,0):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
x^{2}=t\left(x-y\right)\label{eq:5}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align center
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename /home/pb/Documents/lm_gerono.png

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Substituting 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:5"

\end_inset

 into 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:4"

\end_inset

 and expanding the difference of two squares:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
t^{2}\left(x-y\right)^{2}-a^{2}\left(x-y\right)\left(x+y\right)=0
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left(x-y\right)\left(t^{2}\left(x-y\right)-a^{2}\left(x-y\right)\right)=0
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Solving for the second term as it contains 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
x\left(t^{2}-a^{2}\right)-y(t^{2}+a^{2})=0
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So we can substitute 
\begin_inset Formula $y=x\frac{t^{2}-a^{2}}{t^{2}+a^{2}}$
\end_inset

in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:5"

\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
x^{2}-t\left(x-x\frac{t^{2}-a^{2}}{t^{2}+a^{2}}\right)=0
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
x^{2}-x\left(\frac{t\left(t^{2}+a^{2}\right)-t\left(t^{2}-a^{2}\right)}{t^{2}+a}\right)=0
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
x\left(x-\frac{2a^{2}t}{t^{2}+a^{2}}\right)=0
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Which has solutions 
\begin_inset Formula $x=0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $x=\frac{2a^{2}t}{t^{2}+a^{2}}.$
\end_inset

 Then:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
y=\frac{2a^{2}t}{t^{2}+a^{2}}\bullet\frac{t^{2}-a^{2}}{t^{2}+a^{2}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

